#RheumatoidArthritis An autoimmune disorder predominantly of the joints but with many systemic manifestations of chronic #inflammation.
#RheumatoidArthritis  The cause is unknown although there is an association with specific HLA types
#RheumatoidArthritis As with most #autoimmune diseases, RA is more common in women.
#RheumatoidArthritis Chronic synovitis leads to overgrowth, or pannus infection, which damages all the structures surrounding the joint
#RheumatoidArthritis Bilateral, symmetrical joint involvement: PIP joints, MCP joints of hands, and involvement of wrists, knees, and ankles
#RheumatoidArthritis Morning stiffness lasting at least 30 minutes, but often much longer
#RheumatoidArthritis Rheumatoid nodules (20%), most often over bony prominences
#RheumatoidArthritis Ocular symptoms: episcleritis; Lung involvement: pleural effusion and nodules of lung parenchyma
#RheumatoidArthritis Vasculitis skin, bowel, and peripheral nerves
#RheumatoidArthritis Cervical joint involvement, particularly at C1 and C2, which can lead to subluxation
#RheumatoidArthritis Baker cyst may rupture and mimic a #DVT, #Pericarditis and pleural pressure, #Carpaltunnelsyndrome
#RheumatoidArthritis Rheumatoid factor in 70 to 80%.nonspecific and can be associated w/ many #autoimmune and chronic infectious diseases.
#RheumatoidArthritis Anti-cyclic citrulinated peptide (anti-CCP) is more than 80% sensitive and more than 95% specific
#RheumatoidArthritis Radiographs show erosion of joints and #osteopenia, Elevated ESR an C-reactive protein, Normocytic #Anemia
#RheumatoidArthritis #Arthrocentesis is useful on initial presentation to exclude crystal disease and infection if diagnosis is not clear.
#RheumatoidArthritis #Methotrexate: best initial DMARD. Adverse effects are liver toxicity, bone marrow suppression, and pulmonary toxicity
#RheumatoidArthritis Tumor Necrosis Factor Inhibitors (#Inflixumab, #adalimumab, and #etanercept):
#RheumatoidArthritis #Rituximab: Is effective in RA as a DMARD by removing CD20 positive #lymphocytes from circulation.
#RheumatoidArthritis #Hydroxychloroquine:  used a DMARD in cases of mild disease when looking to avoid toxicity of #methotrexate.
#RheumatoidArthritis #NSAIDS are the best initial therapy for the pain of RA.
Juvenile #RheumatoidArthritis is very difficult to define and there is no known etiology
#RheumatoidArthritis; presence of high spiking fever in a young person that has no clearly identified etiology but is associated w/ a rash.
Juvenile #RheumatoidArthritis There is no clear diagnostic test; however #anemia and #leukocytosis are often present. ANA is normal.
Juvenile #RheumatoidArthritis Half of cases improve with aspirin or #NSAIDS. If there is no response, then use #steroids
